tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: Renal function is significantly impaired as indicated by elevated creatinine. Lipid profile shows increased triglycerides and LDL cholesterol, suggesting elevated cardiovascular risk. All other parameters, including liver enzymes, electrolytes, glucose, and proteins, are within normal limits. Recommend further evaluation of renal function and cardiovascular risk management.
